<task id="WKSP-022" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter — ownership validation endpoint filter</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, auth</tags>
    <estimated-effort>3h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation with auth tag — creates an authorization endpoint filter enforcing ownership rules and system layout protection; ADR-008 constraint applies; security-sensitive code</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <role>Senior .NET developer implementing workspace layout API</role>
    <goal>
      Create a WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter as an endpoint filter that validates layout
      ownership for mutation operations (PUT, DELETE) and read-by-ID operations. System layouts
      bypass ownership checks for read access (all users can read them) but reject all write
      and delete attempts with 403 Forbidden.
    </goal>
    <context>
      The BFF API uses endpoint filters (not global middleware) for resource-level authorization
      per ADR-008. The existing DocumentAuthorizationFilter demonstrates this pattern — it
      extracts the resource ID from the route, checks ownership, and short-circuits with 403/404
      if unauthorized. WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter follows the same pattern but adds
      system layout awareness: system layout IDs are well-known constants, and any PUT/DELETE
      targeting a system layout is immediately rejected. For GET by ID, system layouts are
      allowed for all authenticated users. For user layouts, the filter verifies the calling
      user is the owner via Dataverse query or by delegating to WorkspaceLayoutService.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST implement IEndpointFilter (ADR-008)
      - MUST NOT use global middleware for authorization (ADR-008)
      - MUST extract layout ID from route values ({id} parameter)
      - MUST allow all authenticated users to read system layouts (GET)
      - MUST reject PUT and DELETE on system layout IDs with 403 Forbidden and ProblemDetails
      - MUST verify calling user owns the layout for user layout mutations
      - MUST return 404 NotFound with ProblemDetails if layout does not exist
      - MUST return 403 Forbidden with ProblemDetails if user does not own the layout
      - MUST extract user identity from HttpContext.User claims
      - MUST be applied per-endpoint, not globally — only on routes that accept {id} parameter
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/DocumentAuthorizationFilter.cs</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Endpoint filter: public class WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter : IEndpointFilter { public async ValueTask&lt;object?&gt; InvokeAsync(EndpointFilterInvocationContext ctx, EndpointFilterDelegate next) }</pattern>
      <pattern>Route value extraction: ctx.HttpContext.Request.RouteValues["id"]</pattern>
      <pattern>User identity: ctx.HttpContext.User.FindFirst("oid")?.Value for Azure AD object ID</pattern>
      <pattern>Short-circuit: return TypedResults.Problem(detail: "...", statusCode: 403, title: "Forbidden")</pattern>
      <pattern>System layout check: SystemWorkspaceLayouts.IsSystemLayout(layoutId) returns true for well-known GUIDs</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter.cs (new)</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/DocumentAuthorizationFilter.cs (pattern reference)</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutService.cs (from Task 020)</file>
