  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read DocumentAuthorizationFilter.cs to understand the existing endpoint filter pattern — how it extracts route values, checks ownership, and returns ProblemDetails on failure</step>
    <step order="2">Read the endpoint-filters.md pattern for the canonical filter structure and registration approach</step>
    <step order="3">Create WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter.cs in the Api/Filters/ directory implementing IEndpointFilter</step>
    <step order="4">Implement route value extraction — parse the {id} parameter as a GUID; return 400 BadRequest if malformed</step>
    <step order="5">Implement system layout detection — check if the layout ID matches a well-known system layout GUID; for GET requests, allow and call next(); for PUT/DELETE, short-circuit with 403 Forbidden ProblemDetails ("System layouts cannot be modified")</step>
    <step order="6">Implement user layout ownership check — extract the user's Azure AD object ID from HttpContext.User claims, call WorkspaceLayoutService to verify the layout exists and is owned by the calling user; return 404 if not found, 403 if not owned</step>
    <step order="7">Implement the happy path — if all checks pass, call next() to proceed to the endpoint handler</step>
    <step order="8">Run dotnet build to verify compilation succeeds with no errors</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 022 status from pending to completed</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter.cs — endpoint filter for layout ownership and system layout protection</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter implements IEndpointFilter and compiles without errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">GET requests for system layout IDs pass through the filter (allowed for all authenticated users)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PUT and DELETE requests targeting system layout IDs are rejected with 403 Forbidden and a ProblemDetails body stating "System layouts cannot be modified"</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PUT and DELETE requests for user layouts owned by a different user are rejected with 403 Forbidden</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Requests for non-existent layout IDs return 404 NotFound with ProblemDetails</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

